    {
      "id": "sybil_11_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_11",
      "description": "Offered is a museum-grade 2004 Porsche 911 (996.2) Carrera 4S, a definitive example of the analog 911 experience. This specimen features the 3.6L M96/03 flat-six engine equipped with VarioCam Plus, delivering a linear power band and a visceral acoustic profile. The drivetrain is anchored by a precise 6-speed G96/31 manual transaxle and the iconic Turbo-derived wide-body chassis with an all-wheel-drive viscous coupling. Mechanically, this C4S is beyond reproach: the IMS bearing has been proactively replaced with a dual-row ceramic solution, and the rear main seal remains perfectly dry. The factory suspension maintains its original geometry, complemented by four-piston monobloc Brembo calipers and cross-drilled rotors. Every body panel retains its factory-original Arctic Silver Metallic finish with zero imperfections, while the interior's full-leather upholstery shows no evidence of bolster wear or UV degradation. A turn-key investment for the discerning purist.",
